rComments: Genuinely my favourite prof. Would recommend for those interested in cinema & philosophy. Encourages class discussion and in-depth analysis of films.

rComments: Boring! As a person interested in art and all those posh topics, his tangents were brutal and there was no focus or structure in rambling lectures. As a science student, this class is infuriating as everything is abstract and no real review able points were made. Film choices were mixed, some brutal others decent. Easy if writing comes naturally.
Very interesting and intelligent lectures. He's a little tough on grading, but gives you ways to improve.

Fantastic professor! I look up to this man and hope day that I can one day become a brilliant lecturer like him.  Very approachable and really gets the class engaged. I had him for an avant-garde course as well and thoroughly enjoyed it! He's an extremely fair marker and expects you to do all the readings (Which students should be doing anyways)
Very knowledgeable. Welcomes discussion. Can get off on tangents, but they're always interesting. An inquiring mind. Superp class readings.
By far the worst prof I have ever had in university. The worst marker too. He is not a hard marker but just doesn't know how to mark!

Extremely nice and approachable.  He has a way of putting students at ease and participate in class discussions(even though class is small).  Great facilitator of discussion.  Explains things clearly.  I find him VERY attractive.
